# Weft

**AI-Assisted Development Workflow with Code-Generating Agents**

Weft is a CLI tool that orchestrates AI agents to design and implement software features. Each agent has a specific role - from initial design to architecture to **generating executable code**. Agents automatically apply code to isolated feature branches, with human review before merging to main.

## Status

**Current Version:** 0.1.0 (Early Development)

Weft is in active development. Core functionality is working but the system is not yet production-ready.

**What Works Now:**
- **Automated 6-Agent Pipeline:** Full feature development from design to code to tests
- **Language-Agnostic Code Generation:** Agents 02-05 generate code for your configured stack (TypeScript, Python, Go, Rust, etc.)
- **Automatic Code Application:** Code patches applied to feature branch worktrees
- **Test Generation:** Test agent creates comprehensive test suites
- **Multi-Language Support:** Configure your stack in `.weftrc.yaml` (TypeScript/React, Python/Django, Go/Gin, Rust/Actix, etc.)
- Project initialization with `.weftrc.yaml` configuration
- Docker-based runtime with agent watchers
- Feature lifecycle management with Git worktrees
- Claude API integration with structured prompts
- Human review gate at `weft feature review`

**What's Coming:**
- Enhanced observability and tracing
- Offline/local LLM support
- Production deployment guides
- Agent customization UI

**Known Limitations (v0.1):**
- Conversation context uses 60-second timestamp window (UUID-based matching in v0.2)
- Single-threaded agent processing only
- LocalLLM backend not yet implemented (Ollama support in M4)
- No observability/tracing (planned for M3)
- Manual conflict resolution required

See [Troubleshooting](docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md#known-limitations-v01) for details and workarounds.

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.11 or higher
- Docker and Docker Compose
- Claude API key from [console.anthropic.com](https://console.anthropic.com/)

### Installation

Choose the method that works best for you:

#### Option 1: Homebrew (Recommended for macOS/Linux)

```bash
brew tap weftlabs/tap
brew install weft
```

#### Option 2: pipx (Recommended for Python Developers)

```bash
pipx install git+https://github.com/weftlabs/weft-cli.git
```

#### Option 3: Quick Install Script

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/weftlabs/weft-cli/main/install.sh | sh
```

#### Option 4: From Source (For Development)

```bash
git clone https://github.com/weftlabs/weft-cli.git
cd weft-cli
pip install -e .
```

**See [INSTALLATION.md](docs/INSTALLATION.md) for detailed instructions, troubleshooting, and prerequisites.**

### Initialize Your Project

```bash
# Navigate to your project directory
cd ~/projects/my-app

# Initialize Weft (creates .weftrc.yaml and .weft/ directory)
weft init

# Follow the interactive prompts:
# - Project name: my-app
# - Project type: fullstack|backend|frontend
# - AI provider: claude|ollama|other
# - AI history path: ../weft-ai-history (default)
```

### Configure API Key

```bash
# Set your Claude API key
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-your-key-here

# Or create a .env file
echo "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-your-key-here" > .env
```

### Start the Runtime

```bash
# Start Docker containers for agent watchers
weft up

# View logs from a specific agent
weft logs meta --follow

# Stop the runtime
weft down
```

### Your First Feature

```bash
# Create a new feature
weft feature create user-auth

# Start the feature (launches agents)
weft feature start user-auth

# Check status
weft feature status user-auth

# Review outputs and decide (accept/drop/continue)
weft feature review user-auth
```

